
To craete a new repository "myproject",

1. Create a local folder (git repository) for a new project, i.e.,
   mkdir myproject
2. Initialize the git repository
   cd myproject
   git init
3. Perform steps 1 ~ 3 of the section "To add/delete/modify ..." below.
4. Create a new remote repository at github.com from web browser.
5. Register remote repository whose name is "origin" with url "git@github...".
   git remote add origin git@github.com:hbmin/myproject.git
   git push -u origin master


To add/delete/modify files in the project in the future,

1. Modify or add/delete files.
2. git add .
3. git commit -m "message"
4. git push

note: use "git status" to see status at any time.
note: use one of the following commands to clone this project.
      git clone https://github.com/hbmin/sample.git
      git clone git@github.com:hbmin/sample.git
